notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T11:59:30.408Z",maintainer-agent,"Implemented: update-many now derives unmatched requested ids (same CSV split as the list ids filter, dedupe, request order) and reports unmatched_ids + unmatched_count on ALL THREE envelopes — dry_run, apply, and the all-skipped no-op result; fields present (possibly empty) whenever --ids was given, absent for filter-based runs. Partial-success apply behavior unchanged. Spec covers mixed valid/missing ids across dry-run/apply/noop, duplicate requested ids, filter-run absence, fully-matched empty array. Manual verify: {\"updated_count\":2,\"unmatched_ids\":[\"pm-zzzz\"],\"unmatched_count\":1}."
